@startuml
title Viaverse AI Assistant / Support / Safety Intelligence — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor User
actor "Support Agent" as Agent
actor "AI/Ops Admin" as Admin
actor "Domain Services" as Domain
actor "LLM Provider\nor Local Model" as LLM
actor "Knowledge Base\nDocs / Policies / FAQs" as KB

rectangle "AI Assistant / Support Boundary" {
  usecase "Ask AI help\nin app" as Ask
  usecase "Build scoped context\nscreen/job/account state" as Context
  usecase "Apply safety/privacy guardrails" as Guard
  usecase "Generate answer\nor guided action" as Answer
  usecase "Retrieve knowledge\nRAG" as Search
  usecase "Classify intent\nsupport/search/safety" as Intent
  usecase "Suggest next action\nnot auto-execute risky action" as Action
  usecase "Escalate to human support" as Escalate
  usecase "Create support ticket" as Ticket
  usecase "Summarize conversation\nfor support" as Summary
  usecase "Agent replies\nwith AI assistance" as AgentAssist
  usecase "Collect answer feedback" as Feedback
  usecase "Run quality/safety evals" as Evals
  usecase "Manage prompts/policies" as Config
  usecase "Emit events\nAiAsked / Escalated / TicketResolved" as Events
}

User --> Ask
Ask --> Context
Context --> Guard
Guard --> Answer
Context ..> Search : needs knowledge
Search --> Intent
Intent --> Action
Action ..> Escalate : risky/uncertain
Escalate --> Ticket
Ticket --> Summary
Summary --> AgentAssist
AgentAssist --> Feedback
Feedback --> Events
Admin --> Evals
Admin --> Config
Evals --> Events
Domain --> Context
LLM --> Answer
KB --> Search

note bottom
AI can guide, summarize and recommend.
It must not execute risky actions such as payment, refund,
suspension or data deletion without explicit policy-controlled confirmation.
end note
@enduml
